{"author":{"id":"138b13306404778af60b1d60d606624fec41556ddac480b2d5f762806ce84fed"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1783029704,"nonce":"DVmzcM8XV6VUXbPWN82TTkWQLzU=","kind":"plan","title":"`kref show` markdown reflow + global `--plain` ā€” Implementation Plan"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1783029704,"nonce":"Q1mOJCxJZjRhOxz24i+mKVyNEBM=","body":"# `kref show` Markdown Reflow + Global `--plain` Implementation Plan\n\n\u003e **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Rendered markdown reflows hard-wrapped (LLM-authored) source to the display width, and a single global `--plain` flag replaces `list --plain` + `show --raw` as the chrome-free script contract.\n\n**Architecture:** A goldmark-AST-guided preprocessor (`internal/render/unwrap.go`) joins soft-wrapped continuation lines in paragraphs and tight list items before glamour renders; glamour is upgraded v1.0.0 ā†’ `charm.land/glamour/v2` v2.0.1 (v1 mangles blockquote wrapping even on single-line input). `--plain` becomes a persistent root flag mapped per command: `list`/`search` ā†’ TSV, `show` ā†’ verbatim body without header. Stored content is never mutated; `--json` stays byte-faithful.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Go, cobra, goldmark (promoted indirect ā†’ direct), glamour v2, ginkgo/gomega.\n\n**Spec:** kref entry `5d77fa72137c` (accepted). Read it first: `./bin/kref show --raw --no-pager 5d77fa72137c` (or `--plain` once Task 5 lands).\n\n**Ground rules for every task:**\n- Work on branch `feat/show-reflow-plain` (Task 1 creates it from `main`).\n- Build with `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto`. Run package tests as\n  `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto KREF_BETTERLEAKS=/workspace/bin/betterleaks go test ./\u003cpkg\u003e/`.\n  The final gate is `task check` (wires env + lint + e2e correctly).\n- If `~/.gitconfig.llm` exists, commit with `GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL=$HOME/.gitconfig.llm git commit ā€¦`.\n- Stage files by name; never `git add .`/`-A`. No `--amend`, no `--no-verify`.\n- All prototype code below was verified against scratch modules on 2026-07-02 ā€” glamour v2 API compatibility (`NewTermRenderer`, `WithStandardStyle`, `WithStyles`+`ansi.StyleConfig`, `WithWordWrap`, ANSI-to-pipe) and the full `UnwrapMarkdown` behavior table are empirical results, not guesses.\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Upgrade glamour to v2 (`charm.land/glamour/v2`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `go.mod` (glamour dep swap; goldmark stays, becomes direct in Task 2)\n- Modify: `internal/render/render.go:15-17` (imports), `render.go:701-729` (`RenderBody`)\n- Test: `internal/render/render_test.go` (new ANSI-contract spec; existing specs must stay green)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Create the branch**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace \u0026\u0026 git checkout -b feat/show-reflow-plain main\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Write the failing ANSI-contract test**\n\nIn `internal/render/render_test.go`, inside `var _ = Describe(\"RenderBody\", ā€¦)` add:\n\n```go\n\tIt(\"emits ANSI for markdown when color is on (the KREF_COLOR=1 pipe contract)\", func() {\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\trender.RenderBody(\u0026b, \"# Heading\\n\\nsome **bold** prose\", \"text/markdown\", true, 80)\n\t\tExpect(b.String()).To(ContainSubstring(\"\\x1b[\"))\n\t})\n```\n\nThis pins the behavior VHS demos depend on (color forced through a pipe) so the v2 swap can't silently lose it. It passes on v1 too ā€” that's fine; it's a regression guard for this task, not a red/green gate.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Swap the dependency**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace\nGOTOOLCHAIN=auto go mod edit -droprequire github.com/charmbracelet/glamour\nGOTOOLCHAIN=auto go get charm.land/glamour/v2@v2.0.1\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Update imports and `RenderBody` in `internal/render/render.go`**\n\nImports: replace\n\n```go\n\t\"github.com/charmbracelet/glamour\"\n\t\"github.com/charmbracelet/glamour/ansi\"\n```\n\nwith\n\n```go\n\t\"charm.land/glamour/v2\"\n\t\"charm.land/glamour/v2/ansi\"\n```\n\nReplace the whole `RenderBody` function (v1's package-level `glamour.Render(body, \"dark\")` arm is the only API not verified against v2, so the switch collapses into one explicit renderer ā€” same three behaviors, one construction):\n\n```go\n// RenderBody writes body rendered according to contentType: markdown through\n// glamour, recognized code/structured text through chroma (color only), and\n// everything else verbatim. width\u003e0 wraps markdown to that column count; width==0\n// leaves it unwrapped (except colored output, which wraps at 80 to match the\n// old glamour.Render default). Color off keeps output ANSI-free and deterministic.\nfunc RenderBody(w io.Writer, body, contentType string, color bool, width int) {\n\tif content.IsMarkdown(contentType) {\n\t\tstyle := glamour.WithStyles(plainMarkdownStyle)\n\t\tif color {\n\t\t\tstyle = glamour.WithStandardStyle(\"dark\")\n\t\t}\n\t\twrap := width\n\t\tif color \u0026\u0026 wrap == 0 {\n\t\t\twrap = 80\n\t\t}\n\t\tif r, err := glamour.NewTermRenderer(style, glamour.WithWordWrap(wrap)); err == nil {\n\t\t\tif out, rerr := r.Render(body); rerr == nil {\n\t\t\t\tfmt.Fprint(w, out)\n\t\t\t\treturn\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t\t// glamour failure falls through to verbatim so output is never lost.\n\t}\n\tif lexer := content.Lexer(contentType); lexer != \"\" \u0026\u0026 color {\n\t\tif err := quick.Highlight(w, body, lexer, \"terminal256\", \"monokai\"); err == nil {\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tfmt.Fprintln(w, body)\n}\n```\n\n`plainMarkdownStyle` and its `ansi.StyleConfig` literals compile against v2 unchanged (verified).\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Tidy and build**\n\n```bash\nGOTOOLCHAIN=auto go mod tidy \u0026\u0026 GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go build ./...\n```\n\nExpected: clean build; `go.mod` now requires `charm.land/glamour/v2 v2.0.1`, no `github.com/charmbracelet/glamour`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Run the render + cli suites**\n\n```bash\nGOTOOLCHAIN=auto KREF_BETTERLEAKS=/workspace/bin/betterleaks go test ./internal/render/ ./cmd/kref/\n```\n\nExpected: mostly green. v2 shifts blank-line placement slightly in the plain style; if a spec pinning exact rendered output fails (candidates: `RenderBody` \"renders markdown (no raw '# ' marker) in plain mode\", cli \"show (default, piped) renders markdown rather than printing raw source\" ā€” both use `ContainSubstring`, so failures are unlikely), read the actual output and update the expectation deliberately. Do NOT loosen assertions to make noise pass ā€” each change must be explainable as \"v2 formats X differently\".\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add go.mod go.sum internal/render/render.go internal/render/render_test.go\ngit commit -m \"build: upgrade glamour to charm.land/glamour/v2\n\nv1 mangles blockquote word-wrap even for single-line input (orphan words,\ndropped margin markers); v2 renders cleanly. Groundwork for soft-break\nunwrapping (spec 5d77fa72137c). The colored zero-width path now constructs\nits renderer explicitly at the same 80-column default glamour.Render used.\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: `UnwrapMarkdown` ā€” the soft-break unwrapper (TDD)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `internal/render/unwrap.go`\n- Create: `internal/render/unwrap_test.go` (external `render_test` package, like every other test here)\n- Modify: `go.mod` (goldmark becomes a direct require via `go mod tidy`)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing tests**\n\nCreate `internal/render/unwrap_test.go`:\n\n```go\npackage render_test\n\nimport (\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/render\"\n)\n\n// Every entry was verified against a goldmark+glamour scratch harness on\n// 2026-07-02; these are behavioral goldens, not aspirations.\nvar _ = DescribeTable(\"UnwrapMarkdown\",\n\tfunc(in, want string) { Expect(render.UnwrapMarkdown(in)).To(Equal(want)) },\n\n\tEntry(\"empty input passes through\", \"\", \"\"),\n\tEntry(\"single-line paragraph passes through\", \"hello\\n\", \"hello\\n\"),\n\tEntry(\"joins a wrapped paragraph\",\n\t\t\"A paragraph that was wrapped\\nacross three lines by an LLM\\nshould join into one.\\n\",\n\t\t\"A paragraph that was wrapped across three lines by an LLM should join into one.\\n\"),\n\tEntry(\"keeps a trailing-two-space hard break, joins the rest\",\n\t\t\"A hard break line ends here  \\nso this line stays separate\\nbut joins with this one.\\n\",\n\t\t\"A hard break line ends here  \\nso this line stays separate but joins with this one.\\n\"),\n\tEntry(\"keeps a backslash hard break\",\n\t\t\"Backslash hard break\\\\\\nkeeps its newline.\\n\",\n\t\t\"Backslash hard break\\\\\\nkeeps its newline.\\n\"),\n\tEntry(\"joins bullets, nested bullets, and task items, keeping markers\",\n\t\t\"- a bullet wrapped across\\n  two lines joins\\n  - nested bullet also\\n    wrapped joins\\n- [ ] task item wrapped\\n  across lines joins too\\n\",\n\t\t\"- a bullet wrapped across two lines joins\\n  - nested bullet also wrapped joins\\n- [ ] task item wrapped across lines joins too\\n\"),\n\tEntry(\"joins a blockquote paragraph onto one marker line\",\n\t\t\"\u003e a blockquote paragraph\\n\u003e wrapped across lines\\n\u003e joins into one quote line\\n\",\n\t\t\"\u003e a blockquote paragraph wrapped across lines joins into one quote line\\n\"),\n\tEntry(\"joins a lazy blockquote continuation (no marker on line 2)\",\n\t\t\"\u003e lazy continuation quote\\nwithout the marker joins\\n\",\n\t\t\"\u003e lazy continuation quote without the marker joins\\n\"),\n\tEntry(\"leaves a fenced code block untouched\",\n\t\t\"```text\\ncode fence line one\\n  code fence line two stays\\n```\\n\",\n\t\t\"```text\\ncode fence line one\\n  code fence line two stays\\n```\\n\"),\n\tEntry(\"leaves an indented code block untouched\",\n\t\t\"    indented code block\\n    stays exactly as is\\n\",\n\t\t\"    indented code block\\n    stays exactly as is\\n\"),\n\tEntry(\"leaves a GFM table untouched\",\n\t\t\"| col a | col b |\\n|-------|-------|\\n| cell  | cell  |\\n\",\n\t\t\"| col a | col b |\\n|-------|-------|\\n| cell  | cell  |\\n\"),\n\tEntry(\"leaves an ATX heading line untouched\",\n\t\t\"# Heading stays\\n\\npara joins\\nhere\\n\",\n\t\t\"# Heading stays\\n\\npara joins here\\n\"),\n\tEntry(\"leaves a setext heading untouched\",\n\t\t\"setext heading\\nwrapped second line\\n===\\n\",\n\t\t\"setext heading\\nwrapped second line\\n===\\n\"),\n\tEntry(\"joins CRLF input and normalizes line endings to LF\",\n\t\t\"para one wrapped\\r\\nacross crlf lines\\r\\n\",\n\t\t\"para one wrapped across crlf lines\\n\"),\n\tEntry(\"joins loose list item paragraphs\",\n\t\t\"- loose item para\\n  wrapped lines\\n\\n- second loose item\\n\",\n\t\t\"- loose item para wrapped lines\\n\\n- second loose item\\n\"),\n\tEntry(\"preserves a missing trailing newline\",\n\t\t\"no trailing newline para\\nwrapped\",\n\t\t\"no trailing newline para wrapped\"),\n)\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run to verify failure**\n\n```bash\nGOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/render/\n```\n\nExpected: FAIL ā€” `undefined: render.UnwrapMarkdown` (compile error).\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement `internal/render/unwrap.go`**\n\n```go\npackage render\n\nimport (\n\t\"strings\"\n\n\t\"github.com/yuin/goldmark\"\n\t\"github.com/yuin/goldmark/ast\"\n\t\"github.com/yuin/goldmark/extension\"\n\t\"github.com/yuin/goldmark/text\"\n)\n\n// UnwrapMarkdown joins soft-wrapped continuation lines inside paragraphs and\n// tight list items (goldmark TextBlocks) so glamour can reflow them to the\n// display width ā€” glamour renders soft breaks inside list items as literal\n// newlines, which keeps LLM-authored 78-column source unreadably choppy.\n// Hard breaks (trailing two spaces or a backslash) are preserved, and every\n// line outside a paragraph ā€” fences, indented code, tables, headings, HTML,\n// blanks ā€” passes through verbatim. CRLF input comes out LF. Parsing uses the\n// GFM extensions to match glamour's block grammar (a table must not be\n// mistaken for a joinable paragraph).\nfunc UnwrapMarkdown(src string) string {\n\tif src == \"\" {\n\t\treturn src\n\t}\n\tsource := []byte(src)\n\tmd := goldmark.New(goldmark.WithExtensions(extension.GFM))\n\tdoc := md.Parser().Parse(text.NewReader(source))\n\n\t// lineStarts[i] is the byte offset where source line i begins.\n\tlineStarts := []int{0}\n\tfor i, b := range source {\n\t\tif b == '\\n' \u0026\u0026 i+1 \u003c len(source) {\n\t\t\tlineStarts = append(lineStarts, i+1)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tlineOf := func(off int) int { // index of the line containing offset off\n\t\tlo, hi := 0, len(lineStarts)-1\n\t\tfor lo \u003c hi {\n\t\t\tmid := (lo + hi + 1) / 2\n\t\t\tif lineStarts[mid] \u003c= off {\n\t\t\t\tlo = mid\n\t\t\t} else {\n\t\t\t\thi = mid - 1\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn lo\n\t}\n\tlineEnd := func(i int) int { // offset just past line i's content (no \\n, no \\r)\n\t\tend := len(source)\n\t\tif i+1 \u003c len(lineStarts) {\n\t\t\tend = lineStarts[i+1] - 1\n\t\t} else if source[end-1] == '\\n' {\n\t\t\tend--\n\t\t}\n\t\tif end \u003e lineStarts[i] \u0026\u0026 source[end-1] == '\\r' {\n\t\t\tend--\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn end\n\t}\n\thardBreak := func(i int) bool {\n\t\tend, start := lineEnd(i), lineStarts[i]\n\t\tif end \u003e start \u0026\u0026 source[end-1] == '\\\\' {\n\t\t\treturn true\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn end-start \u003e= 2 \u0026\u0026 source[end-1] == ' ' \u0026\u0026 source[end-2] == ' '\n\t}\n\n\t// Multi-line paragraph blocks: first source line -\u003e that block's segments.\n\tjoinStart := map[int][]text.Segment{}\n\tconsumed := map[int]bool{}\n\t_ = ast.Walk(doc, func(n ast.Node, entering bool) (ast.WalkStatus, error) {\n\t\tif !entering {\n\t\t\treturn ast.WalkContinue, nil\n\t\t}\n\t\tif k := n.Kind(); k != ast.KindParagraph \u0026\u0026 k != ast.KindTextBlock {\n\t\t\treturn ast.WalkContinue, nil\n\t\t}\n\t\tlines := n.Lines()\n\t\tif lines.Len() \u003c 2 {\n\t\t\treturn ast.WalkContinue, nil\n\t\t}\n\t\tsegs := make([]text.Segment, lines.Len())\n\t\tfor i := 0; i \u003c lines.Len(); i++ {\n\t\t\tsegs[i] = lines.At(i)\n\t\t}\n\t\tjoinStart[lineOf(segs[0].Start)] = segs\n\t\tfor _, s := range segs[1:] {\n\t\t\tconsumed[lineOf(s.Start)] = true\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn ast.WalkContinue, nil\n\t})\n\n\tvar out strings.Builder\n\tout.Grow(len(source))\n\tfor i := 0; i \u003c len(lineStarts); i++ {\n\t\tif consumed[i] {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tsegs, ok := joinStart[i]\n\t\tif !ok {\n\t\t\tout.Write(source[lineStarts[i]:lineEnd(i)])\n\t\t\tout.WriteByte('\\n')\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\t// Split the block into runs at hard-break boundaries; each run joins\n\t\t// into one output line.\n\t\tvar runs [][]text.Segment\n\t\tcur := []text.Segment{segs[0]}\n\t\tfor _, seg := range segs[1:] {\n\t\t\tif hardBreak(lineOf(cur[len(cur)-1].Start)) {\n\t\t\t\truns = append(runs, cur)\n\t\t\t\tcur = []text.Segment{seg}\n\t\t\t} else {\n\t\t\t\tcur = append(cur, seg)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t\truns = append(runs, cur)\n\t\tfor _, run := range runs {\n\t\t\tfirst := lineOf(run[0].Start)\n\t\t\t// The run's first line keeps its structural prefix (list marker,\n\t\t\t// \"\u003e \", indent); continuation prefixes are dropped by the join.\n\t\t\tout.Write(source[lineStarts[first]:run[0].Start])\n\t\t\tfor j, seg := range run {\n\t\t\t\tln := lineOf(seg.Start)\n\t\t\t\traw := string(source[seg.Start:lineEnd(ln)])\n\t\t\t\tif j \u003c len(run)-1 {\n\t\t\t\t\traw = strings.TrimRight(raw, \" \\t\") // soft junction: collapse to one space\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tif j \u003e 0 {\n\t\t\t\t\tout.WriteByte(' ')\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tout.WriteString(raw)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tout.WriteByte('\\n')\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tres := out.String()\n\tif !strings.HasSuffix(src, \"\\n\") {\n\t\tres = strings.TrimSuffix(res, \"\\n\")\n\t}\n\treturn res\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run tests to verify pass, then tidy**\n\n```bash\nGOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/render/ \u0026\u0026 GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go mod tidy\n```\n\nExpected: PASS, all 17 table entries. `go mod tidy` moves `github.com/yuin/goldmark` from the indirect block to a direct require (same v1.7.13 ā€” it is glamour's own parser, zero new module bytes).\n\nIf golangci later flags `UnwrapMarkdown` for cognitive complexity, extract the `runs` emission loop into an unexported `emitJoinedRuns` helper ā€” do not suppress with nolint.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/render/unwrap.go internal/render/unwrap_test.go go.mod go.sum\ngit commit -m \"feat(render): goldmark-AST soft-break unwrapper\n\nLLM-authored entries arrive hard-wrapped at ~78 columns and glamour never\nreflows list-item continuation lines. UnwrapMarkdown joins paragraph and\ntight-list soft breaks (hard breaks, code, tables untouched) so the renderer\nreceives single-line paragraphs it can wrap to the display width. Not wired\ninto RenderBody yet. Spec 5d77fa72137c.\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Wire unwrapping into `RenderBody`\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `internal/render/render.go` (`RenderBody`, one line)\n- Test: `internal/render/render_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing integration specs**\n\nIn `render_test.go`, inside `var _ = Describe(\"RenderBody width\", ā€¦)` add:\n\n```go\n\tIt(\"reflows a hard-wrapped bullet to the display width\", func() {\n\t\tbody := \"- a bullet that was wrapped\\n  tightly across several\\n  source lines by an LLM\\n\"\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\trender.RenderBody(\u0026b, body, \"text/markdown\", false, 100)\n\t\tExpect(b.String()).To(ContainSubstring(\n\t\t\t\"a bullet that was wrapped tightly across several source lines by an LLM\"))\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"joins wrapped paragraph lines even at width zero (the pipe path)\", func() {\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\trender.RenderBody(\u0026b, \"one two\\nthree four\\n\", \"text/markdown\", false, 0)\n\t\tExpect(b.String()).To(ContainSubstring(\"one two three four\"))\n\t})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run to verify failure**\n\n```bash\nGOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/render/\n```\n\nExpected: FAIL ā€” both new specs